issue_comment_body:
This is an alternative to #206. I'm not sure if it is better, but it feels simpler to me (which is only one dimension of "good" and only so if it actually works properly).  While looking through 206 there was so much going on that I couldn't get confident about it, so I did some experimenting of my own.

@justanotherdot if you could compare this with your version and make some comments that would be great.

@FND your eyes always appreciated.

@sblondon I take that back. I tried to remove the `localized` attribute, but I had to revert that change in e5d75edf3786814 because people started writing non-localized 3rd party providers.

I'll merge this in and re-add `localized = True`.

Thank you so much for your contribution! ✨

@arose 

Correct. This is the result I expect. I made some modifications in #30 so that the wrapper can also just take an AtomGroup, since for large systems there's no need to dump the whole thing in.

Quick question while I'm playing with one of my big membrane protein systems: what's the best way to get `nglview` to render non-protein molecules? Like ions and lipids or even waters?

