The only functional change at the moment is that if you have a ~/.openaddr-logging.json file it will be used to configure logging. Otherwise the same old stderr + optional logfile config is used.

Here's a sample config. I'm not in love with using JSON for config files but it seemed better than adding a YAML dependency.

````
{
    "version": 1,
    "disable_existing_loggers": false,
    "formatters": {
        "simple": {
            "format": "%(relativeCreated)7d %(levelname)06s %(module)12s:%(lineno)-4d %(message)s"
        }
    },
    "handlers": {
        "console": {
            "class": "logging.StreamHandler",
            "level": "DEBUG",
            "formatter": "simple",
            "stream": "ext://sys.stderr"
        }
    },
    "root": {
        "level": "DEBUG",
        "handlers": ["console"]
    },
    "loggers": {
        "openaddr": { "level": "INFO" },
        "openaddr.conform": { "level": "DEBUG" },
        "requests": { "level": "ERROR" }
    }
}
````

